pudl-migration.title: pudl0009 Princeton University Historical Postcard Collection

comments.body: This collection is similar to Grounds and Buildings, in that there is detailed item-level metadata in the METS/MODS from the PUDL that doesn't match the descriptive granularity of the EAD.  One solution would be to make a multivolume work for each component in the EAD and ingest each METS/MODS object as a volume of one of those multivolume works.  A considerable amount of metadata (publishers, multiple subject headings) would be lost this way.

comments.body: @mzelesky let us know what you think we should do with this edge case.

I have checked and double-checked the Lewis circulation policy, and restarted vxws multiple times. I don't know why this location (sciss) doesn't respond the same way as Firestone periodicals. But it's making me think locations connected to periodicals shouldn't be eligible for paging. More often than not, the material could be scanned if it's a periodical. And also, I don't know how many bound periodicals actually circulate.
These will be eligible for scan on demand requests. There is something particularly weird about this record since our fallback options for holdings with no item records.
